message.content:
cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata accepting infinite words with a Muller acceptance condition.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the Wagner hierarchy, which is a hierarchy of logical languages.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve algorithmic techniques for determining the hierarchy.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper may involve analyzing the complexity of the blind counter automata.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the least likely category as the paper does not seem to focus on programming languages specifically.
